name: The Tarnished (Protagonist)
description:
is the   of   and  .
 Compelled by the "Flame of Ambition", the Tarnished endeavors to brandish the   and become  . In their journey throughout the  , they encounter various  , bearers of  , as well as their fellow  .
 A Tarnished of no renown, called to cross the sea of fog to the Lands Between, having been blessed once more by the Grace once thought lost to their kind.  Their origins are unknown, as are their accomplishments prior to their arrival in the Lands Between. 
 The Tarnished begins their journey in the  , off the western coast of  , where they find only the corpse of a   slumped against a wall. After a brief encounter with a  , the Tarnished falls from the precipice and washes up in the  . Although death seems inevitable,  they are found by a mysterious woman riding a spectral steed. The woman grants the Tarnished two flasks: one of   and the other of  . With these blessings, the Tarnished emerges from the damp cavern into the grasslands of  .
 The Tarnished is reunited with the woman once more, and she introduces herself to them as  . Seeing that the Tarnished is maidenless, she offers to play the role of a Finger Maiden, allowing the Tarnished to convert the Runes they collect from their enemies into strength. In return, she requests that the Tarnished bring her with them to the foot of the  .  To aid them further, Melina grants the Tarnished a   which will allow them to call upon her spectral steed, who's name she reveals to be  . Melina further explains to the Tarnished that she is searching for a purpose given to her by her mother inside the Erdtree long ago, and the reason she lives, despite her burnt and spectral state.  She advises the Tarnished to seek the Great Runes: shards of the shattered Elden Ring currently held by the  . 
 Early in their shared journey, Melina extends the Tarnished an invitation to  , the gathering place of Tarnished champions.  Here, the Tarnished meets several of their fellow Tarnished, as well as Roundtable Hold's leader,  .
 The Tarnished claims a Great Rune from one of the   scattered throughout the Lands Between, and is permitted audience with the  ; envoys of the  , and  . Interpreting the words of the Fingers, Enia explains to the Tarnished that the shattering of the Elden Ring has left the land in ruins , and instructs the Tarnished to hunt down the Demigods, who have been renounced by the Greater Will.  Gideon offers the Tarnished further advice, imparting his knowledge of the five Shardbearers known to Roundtable Hold. 
 On their journey, the Tarnished may encounter  , a Demigod and the perpetrator of the  .  The Tarnished may choose to enter her service, aiding her as she treads the dark path of the   and attempts to establish her Order upon the world. 
 After claiming two Great Runes, the Tarnished makes their way to  , the home of   the Grace-Given. Melina regains the ability to govern her own movement and bids the Tarnished farewell, leaving them with Torrent and the ability to convert Runes into strength.  The Tarnished proceeds to the Elden Throne and defeats Morgott, claiming his Great Rune, but when they attempt to pass through the door in the Erdtree's trunk they find the way obscured by impenetrable thorns. Melina appears before the Tarnished once more, and reveals that it is her purpose to help the Tarnished become Elden Lord. In order to do so, however, the Erdtree must be burned to remove the thorns.  And so, the Tarnished begins a new journey with Melina, to the  , upon which rests the giant's forge, and a flame which may burn the Erdtree.
 The Tarnished may encounter a being named  , who reveals to the Tarnished that Melina must offer herself as kindling so that the Erdtree can burn.  Shabriri offers an alternative: the tarnished may take Melina's place as kindling and singe their own flesh instead.  To this end, they must descend below the Royal Capital and meet with the  , setting themselves upon the path to becoming the Lord of Chaos.  Should the Tarnished accept this offer, they will make an enemy of Melina, who vows to hunt them down and kill them if they rise as Lord of Chaos. 
 Whether through Melina's sacrifice or the power of the Frenzied Flame, the Erdtree is set aflame, and the Tarnished is transported to  ; an ancient temple in the sky said to have been crumbling since time immemorial.  In Farum Azula, the Tarnished encounters and kills  , releasing the   upon the Lands Between.  
 The Tarnished returns to Leyndell to find it coated in ash, the Erdtree glowing red above. The Tarnished makes their way through the ruined city, but their path is blocked by Gideon, who attempts to stop them from becoming Elden Lord.  The Tarnished kills Gideon, who asserts with his dying breath his belief that a Tarnished cannot become a Lord, for a man cannot kill a god. 
 The Tarnished once again finds themselves at the Elden Throne. This time they find  , the First Elden Lord and former leader of the Tarnished.  Godfrey reveals that he has come to once more be granted audience with Queen Marika, the goddess of the Lands Between  The two Tarnished duel, and Godfrey is forced to tear the beast Serosh from his back and assume the role of Hoarah Loux.  Nevertheless, the Tarnished defeats Godfrey and approaches the Erdtree.
 Inside the Erdtree, the Tarnished find Marika hanging from a Rune, her body seemingly made of stone. Marika falls from the Rune and her body begins to warp as she assumes the form of  , the second Elden Lord. Radagon fights to protect the Golden Order from the Tarnished, but is bested. From his body emerges the  , a vassal of the Greater Will and embodiment of Order  that became the Elden Ring long ago . Despite its status as a god, the Tarnished fells the Elden Beast, and finally stands before the broken body of Queen Marika. Depending on the decisions they made on their journey, the Tarnished may now decide the fate of the Lands Between. They may repair the Elden Ring and rise as Elden Lord , go with Ranni on her thousand year voyage into the chill night , or become the Lord of Frenzied Flame and incinerate all that divides and distinguishes.

name: Character Outfit
description:
are cosmetics for  . They can be previewed and worn in the  .
 Every character has a Default Outfit, and some have an Alternate Outfit in addition to their Default Outfit. These are automatically unlocked upon obtaining a character.
 Characters play outfit-exclusive   when they equip any outfit, including an Alternate Outfit, that is not their Default Outfit.
 Like all  , outfits also have   ratings. Outfits that are not Default Outfits come in 4-Star and 5-Star qualities. Outfit quality is independent of character quality; all characters' default outfits are of 0-Star quality, and both 4-Star and 5-Star characters have received 4-Star outfits.
 5-Star outfits come with idle, Elemental Skill, and Elemental Burst  ; idle animations; and special visual effects in combat. All of these replace the original ones while the outfit is worn. 4-Star outfits do not include any of these and only change the outfit the character is wearing.
 Certain characters have outfits other than their Default and/or Alternate Outfits; these are unofficially known as "Themed Outfits." Themed Outfits can be purchased from the Character Outfit Shop, accessed from  . Some themed outfits can be obtained from limited-time   for free and become available for purchase from the Character Outfit Shop after the limited-time Event ends.
 4-star themed outfits normally cost  , while 5-star themed outfits normally cost  . If discounted, they cost   and  , respectively.
 The player can purchase or obtain a Themed Outfit for a character even if the character has not yet been obtained. The acquisition art for the outfit can be viewed in the  , and the outfit itself will be available to wear immediately after obtaining the character.

name: Traci
description:
Traci  was originally the name of a     and the cut fourth playable protagonist in  . She had around five to six scenes  written by  , but he later made the decision to remove her due to the increasing complexity of the branching narrative. 
 Her name was repurposed in the final game to refer to all WR400 androids. It is unknown if all WR400 androids were also originally named "Traci" or if it was a unique name that she chose for herself.
 There is little known about Traci. According to  , Traci was going to disguise herself as a human and work as a journalist, where she could attempt to â€œtip the scales in favor of one side or the other" depending on the player's choices. The artbook also uses the name "Nathalie" to refer to her, likely to avoid confusion with the repurposed name. According to concept artist Mikael Leger, "Her initial story arc was amazing" and describes her as   Traci.  He also confirms that "Nathalie" was an alias she could assume as part of her undercover journalism work.  
 There is concept art depicting Traci at  . It is unknown what circumstances would have led to this scene taking place.  
 According to concept artist Mikael Leger, there was a scene where Traci was going to be nude under a white coat.   This was probably going to take place during her chapter at the  , as she appears to be wearing the same white coat in the concept art of those deleted chapters.  
 It is unknown what Traci's personality would have been like. 
 Traci is depicted as a young female android with shoulder-length blonde hair and brown eyes. All "Traci" models in the Eden Club shared this exact same appearance. 
 Industry insider Tom Henderson has stated that Traci would have been able to "morph her face and body" as part of her abilities as a  . It is possible that this would have played into her ability to disguise herself for her work as a journalist.  
 Concept art of the Eden Club depicts Traci wearing a lacy black dress and a lingerie set. Later, she is shown wearing a knee-length black coat with heels at Ferndale Station and the Eden Club.      
 Traci's concept art uses the likeness of Israeli-American actress Alona Tal. Tom Henderson has also stated that American actress Amber Heard was used as inspiration for her.
